        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Penrose, or 20 miles northwest of Pueblo, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinon and Pueblo West.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
